The paper deals with a process algebra that uses propositional logic to describe and analyze systems. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. Additionally, the paper introduces a version of the process algebra built on a paraconsistent propositional logic, which is related to the field of paraconsistent logic (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the potential applications of the process algebra in dealing with self-contradictory states, which could be relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents a formalism for describing and analyzing systems, which could be relevant to the field of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
